I wonder if using specialized experts is a better approach to the network as a whole being more general and efficient

the problem with doing this instead is it would mess up our server rewards structure. 

if I'm not mistaken we do something similar with the synergy calculations in the validators.
but i believe it's not fully able to capture the separation/specialization of experts/domains
this paper would suggest "validators" would learn how to identify the domain of a document/sequence and which (single) expert is best
that's interesting, they use a decay parameter to reduce importance on early posteriori
The key is to have validators focus on a subset of problems, rejecting neurons that do not fall within the problem schema
The current framework only applies to text models, and I understand images being a next phase
But the focus should be problem agnostic, let validators offer external api services to consumers
And neuron can focus on specific problems
This can fragment the weight matrix into a factorized set of smaller weight matrixes, which hopefully dampens the quadratic scaling with the number of neurons
It also diversifies the problem set for numerous business use cases, which is good if you want to funnel outside value into Tao
Like you can have some validator work on stable diffusion, others on object detection, others on text models
The incentive distribution doesn’t have to change either, validator just ignore neurons that do not meet the output/input schemas that match the problem in question
This forces the network into subgraphs, which scales better than n^2
